# Copy to `.env` / `.env.local` (not committed). Vite exposes only vars prefixed with VITE_.

# Google Sheets — Trending Destinations (full site refresh loads latest rows)
# 1) Create a spreadsheet with tabs named exactly: TripsMaster, TripPackages, TripHotels, TripItinerary, TripDepartures
#    Optional: add tab **HeroCollage** (see public/sheet-templates/HeroCollage.csv) for hero collage images — any https URL or Google Drive share link.
#    TripsMaster.category must be one of: international | domestic | group (see public/sheet-templates/README.txt)
# 2) File → Share → General access: "Anyone with the link" → Viewer
# 3) Spreadsheet ID is the long id in the URL: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/THIS_PART/edit
VITE_GOOGLE_TRIPS_SPREADSHEET_ID=1WqGSNaNHNoBAJOSIYQKTpXhOPgBf_ibX5iE2g09mc4k

# Optional: if your hero collage tab is not named HeroCollage, set the exact tab name here
# VITE_GOOGLE_HERO_COLLAGE_SHEET_NAME=My Collage Tab
